  "authors": [],
  "body": {
    "comment": "I vote YES on \"Cardano Builder DAO\" because Cardano needs a practical funding path for smaller established builders that can struggle to compete with large Treasury\nproposals, and this DAO has already completed two funding rounds, allocated funds across 34 proposals, and returned unused ADA. I see the model as a useful way to bring\nexpert builder review and proposed DRep oversight closer to projects that can grow users, transactions, and TVL. The 20M ADA ask and delegation of funding decisions are\nsignificant risks, so I expect transparent recipient-level reporting, independent KPI verification, clear conflict disclosures, milestone gates, and a credible path to\nsustainability. This vote gives a proven but still evolving model a chance; it is not an automatic endorsement of recurring Treasury funding."
  },
  "hashAlgorithm": "blake2b-256"
}